<paragraph blockId="199.[151,1437,541,2006]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,721,746]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Description.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[363,467,721,746]" captionStart="FIGURE 126" captionStartId="200.[151,250,1226,1248]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,303,1204]" captionTargetId="figure@200.[151,1436,303,1204]" captionTargetPageId="200" captionText="FIGURE 126. Leucosolenia salpinx sp. nov., a – b, light microscopic images of two individual tubes together belonging to the holotype RMNH Por. 9743, c, light microscopic image of the tube wall showing tangential triactines and echinating diactines, d, apical aperture showing fringe of diactines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273076/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Figs 126</figureCitation>
a–d) Groups of tiny, individual, olynthus-type tubes attached to the tails of 
<taxonomicName class="Demospongiae" family="Tetillidae" genus="Tetilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirophorida" pageId="199" pageNumber="200" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="pentatriaena">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Tetilla pentatriaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens. Shape trumpet-like (
<figureCitation box="[691,799,757,782]" captionStart="FIGURE 126" captionStartId="200.[151,250,1226,1248]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,303,1204]" captionTargetId="figure@200.[151,1436,303,1204]" captionTargetPageId="200" captionText="FIGURE 126. Leucosolenia salpinx sp. nov., a – b, light microscopic images of two individual tubes together belonging to the holotype RMNH Por. 9743, c, light microscopic image of the tube wall showing tangential triactines and echinating diactines, d, apical aperture showing fringe of diactines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273076/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Figs 126</figureCitation>
a–b), tapering from a wide apical aperture to a thin attachment tail. Apical aperture surrounded by a fringe of trichoxeas (
<figureCitation box="[928,1025,793,818]" captionStart="FIGURE 126" captionStartId="200.[151,250,1226,1248]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,303,1204]" captionTargetId="figure@200.[151,1436,303,1204]" captionTargetPageId="200" captionText="FIGURE 126. Leucosolenia salpinx sp. nov., a – b, light microscopic images of two individual tubes together belonging to the holotype RMNH Por. 9743, c, light microscopic image of the tube wall showing tangential triactines and echinating diactines, d, apical aperture showing fringe of diactines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273076/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Fig. 126</figureCitation>
d). Tube body hairy (
<figureCitation box="[1257,1354,793,818]" captionStart="FIGURE 126" captionStartId="200.[151,250,1226,1248]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,303,1204]" captionTargetId="figure@200.[151,1436,303,1204]" captionTargetPageId="200" captionText="FIGURE 126. Leucosolenia salpinx sp. nov., a – b, light microscopic images of two individual tubes together belonging to the holotype RMNH Por. 9743, c, light microscopic image of the tube wall showing tangential triactines and echinating diactines, d, apical aperture showing fringe of diactines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273076/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Fig. 126</figureCitation>
a), with long single trichoxeas and microdiactines protruding at right or oblique angles from the body. Length of tubes 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="199" pageNumber="200" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
, width of the tubes 200–250 µm. Color in alcohol transparent-whitish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="199.[151,1437,541,2006]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,901,926]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Skeleton.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[326,428,901,926]" captionStart="FIGURE 126" captionStartId="200.[151,250,1226,1248]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,303,1204]" captionTargetId="figure@200.[151,1436,303,1204]" captionTargetPageId="200" captionText="FIGURE 126. Leucosolenia salpinx sp. nov., a – b, light microscopic images of two individual tubes together belonging to the holotype RMNH Por. 9743, c, light microscopic image of the tube wall showing tangential triactines and echinating diactines, d, apical aperture showing fringe of diactines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273076/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Figs 126</figureCitation>
c–d) Undifferentiated skeleton consisting of tangential sagittal triactines, tetractines and long thin trichoxeas, together forming the wall of the ascon-type sponge body. Long trichoxeas curve out from the skeleton and protrude far beyond the surface. Microdiactines are lodged in the skeleton between the triactines. Towards the thin tapering end, long thin trichoxeas become proportionally dominant, and at the end only trichoxeas are found in the skeleton.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="199.[151,1437,541,2006]" box="[199,1028,1081,1106]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,1081,1106]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Spicules.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[319,417,1081,1106]" captionStart="FIGURE 127" captionStartId="201.[151,250,1583,1605]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1561]" captionTargetId="figure@201.[151,1436,193,1561]" captionTargetPageId="201" captionText="FIGURE 127. Leucosolenia salpinx sp. nov., a – e, SEM images of the spicules of the holotype RMNH Por. 9743, a, sagittal triactine with very long unpaired actine of the tube walls, a 1, detail of a, b – b 1, triactines with variable unpaired actine length, c, – c 1, tetractines, c 2, detail of c, d, long diactine, d 1, faintly spined ending of d, e, short spined diactine, e 1, detail of e." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273077/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Figs 127</figureCitation>
a–e) Triactines, tetractines, trichoxeas, microdiactines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="199.[151,1437,541,2006]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">
Triactines, sagittal, with straight, long, unpaired actine, divisible more or less clearly into (1) those with short, recurved, paired actines and the longest unpaired actines (
<figureCitation box="[802,902,1153,1178]" captionStart="FIGURE 127" captionStartId="201.[151,250,1583,1605]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1561]" captionTargetId="figure@201.[151,1436,193,1561]" captionTargetPageId="201" captionText="FIGURE 127. Leucosolenia salpinx sp. nov., a – e, SEM images of the spicules of the holotype RMNH Por. 9743, a, sagittal triactine with very long unpaired actine of the tube walls, a 1, detail of a, b – b 1, triactines with variable unpaired actine length, c, – c 1, tetractines, c 2, detail of c, d, long diactine, d 1, faintly spined ending of d, e, short spined diactine, e 1, detail of e." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273077/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Fig. 127</figureCitation>
a,a1), which are also slightly fusiform, unpaired actines 281– 
<emphasis box="[292,334,1190,1214]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">337</emphasis>
–452 
<date box="[397,432,1190,1214]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">x 2</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[447,482,1190,1214]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">4.4</emphasis>
–6 µm, paired actines 36– 
<emphasis box="[774,802,1189,1214]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">46</emphasis>
– 
<date box="[817,866,1189,1214]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200" value="1959-10">59 x</date>
1.5– 
<emphasis box="[923,958,1190,1214]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">3.1</emphasis>
–4 µm, and (2) those with variable lengths of unpaired actines (
<figureCitation box="[387,493,1225,1250]" captionStart="FIGURE 127" captionStartId="201.[151,250,1583,1605]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1561]" captionTargetId="figure@201.[151,1436,193,1561]" captionTargetPageId="201" captionText="FIGURE 127. Leucosolenia salpinx sp. nov., a – e, SEM images of the spicules of the holotype RMNH Por. 9743, a, sagittal triactine with very long unpaired actine of the tube walls, a 1, detail of a, b – b 1, triactines with variable unpaired actine length, c, – c 1, tetractines, c 2, detail of c, d, long diactine, d 1, faintly spined ending of d, e, short spined diactine, e 1, detail of e." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273077/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Figs 127</figureCitation>
b,b1,b2), which are straight and not fusiform, and possess relatively longer paired actines, which are more gradually curved, unpaired actines 51– 
<emphasis box="[862,904,1261,1286]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">169</emphasis>
–315 x 2.5– 
<emphasis box="[1038,1073,1262,1286]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">3.9</emphasis>
–5 µm, paired actines 27– 
<emphasis box="[1366,1394,1262,1286]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">74</emphasis>
– 
<date pageId="199" pageNumber="200" value="1999-10">99 x</date>
2.5– 
<emphasis box="[221,256,1298,1322]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">3.4</emphasis>
–5 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="199.[151,1437,541,2006]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">
Tetractines (
<figureCitation box="[338,443,1333,1358]" captionStart="FIGURE 127" captionStartId="201.[151,250,1583,1605]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1561]" captionTargetId="figure@201.[151,1436,193,1561]" captionTargetPageId="201" captionText="FIGURE 127. Leucosolenia salpinx sp. nov., a – e, SEM images of the spicules of the holotype RMNH Por. 9743, a, sagittal triactine with very long unpaired actine of the tube walls, a 1, detail of a, b – b 1, triactines with variable unpaired actine length, c, – c 1, tetractines, c 2, detail of c, d, long diactine, d 1, faintly spined ending of d, e, short spined diactine, e 1, detail of e." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273077/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Figs 127</figureCitation>
c,c1,c2), of variable form, with straight unpaired actines much shorter than those of the triactines, apical actine usually much shorter than the basal and paired actines, usually slightly sagittal but occasionally almost equiradiate, unpaired actines 42– 
<emphasis box="[756,798,1406,1430]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">154</emphasis>
–282 
<date box="[863,897,1406,1430]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">x 3</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[913,948,1406,1430]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">3.9</emphasis>
–6 µm, paired actines 24– 
<emphasis box="[1244,1272,1406,1429]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">75</emphasis>
– 
<date box="[1287,1357,1405,1430]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200" value="1996-10-03">96 x 3</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[1373,1408,1406,1430]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">3.3</emphasis>
–4 µm, apical actines 14– 
<emphasis box="[403,431,1442,1466]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">24</emphasis>
– 
<date box="[446,514,1442,1466]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200" value="1932-10-02">32 x 2</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[529,564,1442,1466]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">2.9</emphasis>
–4 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="199.[151,1437,541,2006]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">
Long trichoxeas (
<figureCitation box="[405,514,1477,1502]" captionStart="FIGURE 127" captionStartId="201.[151,250,1583,1605]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1561]" captionTargetId="figure@201.[151,1436,193,1561]" captionTargetPageId="201" captionText="FIGURE 127. Leucosolenia salpinx sp. nov., a – e, SEM images of the spicules of the holotype RMNH Por. 9743, a, sagittal triactine with very long unpaired actine of the tube walls, a 1, detail of a, b – b 1, triactines with variable unpaired actine length, c, – c 1, tetractines, c 2, detail of c, d, long diactine, d 1, faintly spined ending of d, e, short spined diactine, e 1, detail of e." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273077/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Figs 127</figureCitation>
d,d1), curved, in a large size variation, those of the main body and the fringe apparently indistinguishable, but those oblique to the surface of the wall and of the thinly tapering distal end of the body clearly longer than the others, with pointed ends frequently finely spined, 310– 
<emphasis box="[1098,1140,1549,1574]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">468</emphasis>
–984 x 1.5– 
<emphasis box="[1273,1308,1550,1574]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">1.8</emphasis>
–2.5 µm
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="199.[151,1437,541,2006]" box="[199,1159,1585,1610]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">
Microdiactines (
<figureCitation box="[382,485,1585,1610]" captionStart="FIGURE 127" captionStartId="201.[151,250,1583,1605]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1561]" captionTargetId="figure@201.[151,1436,193,1561]" captionTargetPageId="201" captionText="FIGURE 127. Leucosolenia salpinx sp. nov., a – e, SEM images of the spicules of the holotype RMNH Por. 9743, a, sagittal triactine with very long unpaired actine of the tube walls, a 1, detail of a, b – b 1, triactines with variable unpaired actine length, c, – c 1, tetractines, c 2, detail of c, d, long diactine, d 1, faintly spined ending of d, e, short spined diactine, e 1, detail of e." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273077/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Figs 127</figureCitation>
e,e1), straight, entirely spined, 72– 
<emphasis box="[869,911,1586,1610]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">151</emphasis>
–270 x 1.5– 
<emphasis box="[1044,1079,1586,1610]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">2.0</emphasis>
–3 µm.
</paragraph>
